\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Why are we in such a hurry?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The Minder and his Mazid leave tonight. So you must leave tonight!}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 But the weather. The wagon will get all chewed up.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Salavan took close to his eyes. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She wanted to point out that sending out a wagon that\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s supposed to draw dry would kill it. She couldn\u8217\'92t do that. She was as proud of this wagon as she was of her son\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 it was just as clean and sturdy, and both she\u8217\'92d built herself. If she were to draw it in the rain, the water would swell the wheels against the shrunk-on iron tire. When the wheel eventually dries out, it will crack, and cracks mean gaps for the sand to enter. Sand will willow its way into the wax-greased innards of the hubs and grind against the bronze bushings. She needed time to take prophylactic measures to guard against this inevitability.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Salavan knew what she thinking.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Damn your wagon, woman! If you don\u8217\'92t stick this goddamn wagon on the end of that column, then by Schisol\u8217\'92s shadow, I will add you to back of this cart!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lorba gulped.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Now go!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The winding route down to the bottom of Meskalim\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s hill was always. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 At the bottom the Hrkan troops were, all of them unusually shrouded in brown robes. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lorba called out to the captain.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I have orders from the governor.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What orders?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m to attach myself to the column.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The captain took the paper from from Lorba\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s hand and }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 How dare he talk like this. I am a scribe! My luck I should put under him. Guild of Lords  has lost it.}
